The paper addresses the problem of searching action proposals in video clips, which is a task related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel actionness estimation method and an optimization objective, which involves designing algorithms and models, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves tracking and inference, which are related to machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. The paper uses datasets and evaluates its performance, which is related to multimedia and information retrieval, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves searching and inference, which are related to information retrieval and optimization, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
